{
  "monologue": "Your current behavior score sits just below midrange, and your profile shows high sensitivity to stress and evening cues. You respond well to ultra-simple, low-decision tasks that still create a sense of control. A fresh micro-action after your breathing adds a tiny, non-food cue to reinforce cue-response pairing and keep momentum without adding cognitive load. Tracking urges and mood will help fine-tune the rotation toward the next step and the target behavior level.",
  "utterance": "Tonight, after your two-minute slow diaphragmatic breathing, add a fresh 60-second micro-action in place: 20 seconds of gentle torso twists, 20 seconds of ankle circles, and 20 seconds of wrist stretches. Then resume the stretches for another minute and log your urge and mood. This small rotation preserves structure while introducing a slightly new movement to support steady progress toward BED management. If urges rise, we can adapt the micro-actions or duration in future sessions.",
  "endkey": false
}
